all needed packages

library("ggplot2")
library("tidyverse")
##  Attaching packages  tidyverse 1.2.1 
##  tibble  1.4.2      purrr   0.2.4
##  tidyr   0.8.0      dplyr   0.7.4
##  readr   1.1.1      stringr 1.3.0
##  tibble  1.4.2      forcats 0.3.0
##  Conflicts  tidyverse_conflicts() 
##  dplyr::filter() masks stats::filter()
##  dplyr::lag()    masks stats::lag()
drug_tb <- read_delim("Drug_Poisoning_Mortality_by_State__United_States-2.csv", "\t", escape_double = FALSE, trim_ws = TRUE)
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   State = col_character(),
##   Year = col_integer(),
##   Sex = col_character(),
##   `Age Group` = col_character(),
##   `Race and Hispanic Origin` = col_character(),
##   Deaths = col_integer(),
##   Population = col_integer(),
##   `Crude Death Rate` = col_double(),
##   `Standard Error for Crude Rate` = col_double(),
##   `Lower Confidence Limit for Crude Rate` = col_double(),
##   `Upper Confidence Limit for Crude Rate` = col_double(),
##   `Age-adjusted Rate` = col_double(),
##   `Standard Error for Age-adjusted Rate` = col_double(),
##   `Lower Confidence Limit for Age-adjusted Rate` = col_double(),
##   `Upper Confidence Limit for Age-adjusted Rate` = col_double(),
##   `State Crude Rate in Range` = col_character(),
##   `US Crude Rate` = col_double(),
##   `US Age-adjusted Rate` = col_double()
## )

Drug poisoning mortality in different age group in the United States (1999-2016)

drug_tb %>% filter(State == "United States", `Age Group` != "All Ages", Sex == "Both Sexes") %>%
  ggplot(., aes(x=Year, y=`Crude Death Rate`, fill=`Age Group`))+
  geom_bar(stat="identity", position=position_dodge())+
  theme_bw()

Crude death rate for drug poisoning by Race and Hispanic Origin from 1999 to 2016

drug_tb %>% filter(State == "United States", `Age Group` == "All Ages", Sex == "Both Sexes") %>%
  ggplot(., aes(x=Year, y=`Crude Death Rate`,color=`Race and Hispanic Origin`))+
  geom_line()

Boxplot of death rate for drug poisoning by Race and Hispanic Origin

drug_tb %>% filter(State == "United States", `Age Group` == "All Ages", Sex == "Both Sexes") %>%
  ggplot(., aes(x=`Race and Hispanic Origin`, y=`Crude Death Rate`))+
  geom_boxplot(aes(fill=`Race and Hispanic Origin`))+
  guides(fill=FALSE) + 
  coord_flip() +
  theme_bw()

The age group pattern of death rate by Race and Hispanic Origin

drug_tb %>% filter(State == "United States", `Age Group` != "All Ages", Sex == "Both Sexes") %>%
  ggplot(., aes(x=`Age Group`, y= `Crude Death Rate`, fill=`Race and Hispanic Origin`))+
  geom_bar(stat="identity", position=position_dodge())+
  facet_grid(`Race and Hispanic Origin` ~ .) +
  guides(fill=FALSE) +
  coord_flip() +
  theme_bw()

Age-adjusted death rates for drug poisoning in different state

color = c(rgb(110, 117, 164, max=255), rgb(155, 144, 194, max=255), rgb(58, 143, 183, max=255), rgb(51, 166,184, max=255), rgb(105, 176, 172, max=255), rgb(145, 173, 122, max=255), rgb(202, 173,95, max=255), rgb(246, 197, 85, max=255), rgb(251, 150, 110, max=255), rgb(208, 90, 110, max=255))
drug_tb %>% 
   mutate(., `Age-adjusted rate gruop` = case_when(
     .$`Age-adjusted Rate` < 5 ~ "0-4.9", 
     .$`Age-adjusted Rate` < 10 & .$`Age-adjusted Rate` >= 5 ~ "05-9.9",
     .$`Age-adjusted Rate` < 15 & .$`Age-adjusted Rate` >= 10 ~ "10-14.9",
     .$`Age-adjusted Rate` < 20 & .$`Age-adjusted Rate` >= 15 ~ "15-19.9",
     .$`Age-adjusted Rate` < 25 & .$`Age-adjusted Rate` >= 20 ~ "20-24.9",
     .$`Age-adjusted Rate` < 30 & .$`Age-adjusted Rate` >= 25 ~ "25-29.9",
     .$`Age-adjusted Rate` < 35 & .$`Age-adjusted Rate` >= 30 ~ "30-34.9",
     .$`Age-adjusted Rate` < 40 & .$`Age-adjusted Rate` >= 35 ~ "35-39.9",
     .$`Age-adjusted Rate` < 45 & .$`Age-adjusted Rate` >= 40 ~ "40-44.9",
     .$`Age-adjusted Rate` > 45 ~ "45-55")) %>% 
  filter(State != "United States") %>%
  ggplot(., aes(Year, State, fill = factor(`Age-adjusted rate gruop`))) + 
  geom_tile(colour = "white") + 
  scale_fill_manual(values = color) +
  scale_x_continuous(expand=c(0,0)) +
  theme(legend.title = element_text(size = 10),
        legend.text = element_text(size = 8),
        axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 300, vjust = 1, size = 10, hjust = 0, colour = "black")) +
  labs(fill="Age-adjusted death rate")
